{"type":"message","id":"3fba8b75","parentId":"7955cf51","timestamp":"2026-03-21T23:31:17.913Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4003\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 19:31 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nlets build this A minimal version using existing tools:\n\nState encoder: A small autoencoder on top of LLM embeddings (freeze the LLM, just learn the compression)\nCausal layer: Build a causal graph from interventions — use a small RL environment (like a grid world) where causal structure is discoverable\nCompositional reasoning: Program synthesis on top of the causal graph — given a goal, synthesize a \"program\" (sequence of causal interventions)\nTest: Does this system generalize to novel goals that weren't in training, using fewer parameters than a comparable LLM?"}],"timestamp":1774135877909}}
