{"type":"message","id":"7893d69c","parentId":"6f884a6c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:11:53.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants a way to save topics for later - like a /hold1, /hold2 command system to bookmark topics to revisit later. This is a productivity/organization feature for the assistant.\n\nLet me think about how to implement this:\n\n1. Create a `holds.md` file in the workspace to store held topics\n2. Create a simple command system - when the user types `/hold1`, `/hold2` etc., it saves the current topic/context to the holds file\n3. Also need a way to retrieve/recall those holds - maybe `/showholds` or `/holds`\n\nActually, I can do this without any special command parsing - OpenClaw will just pass the message to me. I can check if the message starts with `/hold` and act accordingly.\n\nLet me create:\n1. A `holds.md` file to store the topics\n2. A simple mechanism to add/view/clear holds\n\nSince this is Zach's personal assistant workspace (C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/), I should implement this here.\n\nLet me create the holds system.","thinkingSignature":"05c30e1f934747a1f9be69f58994caab2b77af6f096a80e8dd9f520f096f9237"},{"type":"text","text":"Good call — let me set that up.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x0ilwh5445h1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/holds.md","content":"# Holds — Topics to Revisit Later\n\n> Use `/hold1`, `/hold2`, etc. to save topics. `/holds` to see all. `/clearhold1` to clear.\n\n## Active Holds\n\n<!-- Empty — add holds with /hold1, /hold2, etc. -->\n\n---\n\n## Archive (cleared holds)\n\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":348,"cacheRead":1307,"cacheWrite":24512,"totalTokens":26210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774138303623}}
