{"type":"message","id":"943bee10","parentId":"49ef1160","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:15:14.342Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4011\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 20:15 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nif i do the command for new is it going to save the holds still?"}],"timestamp":1774138514338}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4d6a79e","parentId":"943bee10","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:15:23.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking if starting a new session (like a fresh conversation or after some cleanup) will preserve the holds.md file. The holds.md is stored in the workspace directory, which should persist across sessions. Let me reassure him about this.","thinkingSignature":"0d9d94ad72dad6ddae35563019c1e90898d32c0b6c7526f86f4b24105e6869b6"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes — `holds.md` lives in your workspace (`~/.openclaw/workspace/holds.md`), which persists across sessions. New conversation, new day, whatever — the file stays.\n\nThe holds are yours until you explicitly clear them with `/clearhold1`, `/clearhold2`, etc.\n\nWant me to scaffold the causal-minimal project before you go?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":125,"cacheRead":26635,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26760,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774138514341}}
