{"type":"message","id":"1d8c2019","parentId":"bed779dd","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:16:32.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking how to reference a hold in a future conversation. I should explain that they can just mention it in chat - like \"bring up /hold1\" or \"what's in /hold1\" or \"let's work on /hold1\". The AI will read the holds.md file and know what they're referring to.","thinkingSignature":"8aa76f018fbc8fbafe859d101d94b7dcb712e04192ee5e0520878548862606d6"},{"type":"text","text":"Just mention it naturally:\n\n- **\"let's look at /hold1\"**\n- **\"what's in my holds?\"**\n- **\"work on /hold2\"**\n- **\"/holds\"** to see all of them\n\nI'll read `holds.md` at the start of every session (it's in my workspace boot sequence), so I'll always know what your holds are. Just drop the slot number and I'll pull it up.\n\nYou don't need special syntax — I'm reading the file, not relying on memory."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":175,"cacheRead":26503,"cacheWrite":300,"totalTokens":27021,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774138586561}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8f8e6c1","parentId":"1d8c2019","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:19:46.752Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4015\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 20:19 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\ni feel like the more you read at the beginning the larger the latency and the larger the cache chunk used when conversation begins and you shouldnt read the entire holds folder at launch but just know its there and a super short title or summary of each one you are quite slow. How can we speed you up and how can we make you inventive without api calls?"}],"timestamp":1774138786749}}
{"type":"message","id":"308d798e","parentId":"f8f8e6c1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:19:59.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is pointing out a real performance issue - reading files at session startup adds latency and burns tokens. He's right. The AGENTS.md says to read SOUL.md, USER.md, today's/yesterday's memory files, MEMORY.md, CONTEXT.md, memory/active-projects.md - that's a lot of files before I can even respond.\n\nThe key insight here is:\n1. I should only read what's strictly necessary at startup\n2. Holds should have minimal footprint - just the fact that they exist + a short title\n3. Don't read entire files, just know the structure and load on demand\n\nLet me think about what's actually needed at startup vs what's nice-to-have:\n\n\nAt minimum I only really need IDENTITY.md and USER.md to know who I'm talking to and who I am. Everything else can be deferred - holds, memory files, project context - until they're actually relevant. The holds file especially should be tiny, just slot numbers with one-line summaries so I don't waste bandwidth parsing it. Instead of reading everything upfront, I should build knowledge about what's available rather than consuming the actual content - that way I know where to look when something's needed without paying the cost upfront.","thinkingSignature":"c3b7b3b8e58f944c4aa2207468d72ef24d5235b2976da772dd0bc9b45cfc3c8f"},{"type":"text","text":"He's not wrong. Here's the fix:\n\n**Startup reads should be minimal:**\n- `IDENTITY.md` + `USER.md` only — 10 lines total\n- Everything else: load **on demand**, not up front\n\n**Holds should be a lightweight index, not content:**\n\n```\n/hold1 | causal-minimal project\n/hold2 | \n/hold3 | \n```\n\nOne line per slot. I **know** holds exist — I don't need to read the full content until you reference one.\n\n**The general principle:** Don't pay the read cost until the data is actually needed. \"File exists\" metadata is free; parsing content isn't.\n\nWant me to trim the startup sequence down to just IDENTITY + USER, and rebuild `holds.md` as a minimal index?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":404,"cacheRead":26722,"cacheWrite":382,"totalTokens":27551,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774138786751}}
