{"type":"message","id":"dd819e8e","parentId":"be6e1a55","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:46:00.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me summarize for Zach what I've compiled so he can pass the info to the next session.","thinkingSignature":"b08eda47dd524bfec9da3332bd7db2b8dcabcbdc044c194e456338f8364b8591"},{"type":"text","text":"Saved. Here's what I've compiled for `/hold2`:\n\n---\n\n**Goal:** Own gateway — replace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean context layer\n\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md alone is 54KB raw. We can't change OpenClaw's core behavior, but we can build our own layer.\n\n**The setup:**\n- Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) → vLLM + fastapi endpoint\n- OpenClaw routes to our endpoint instead of OpenAI/MiniMax\n- We own: session state, context assembly, system prompts, on-demand file loading\n\n**What we control:** Everything about the prompt. No forced injection of files we don't need every turn.\n\n**What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n\n**Tech stack for the endpoint:** Python + vLLM + fastapi (or similar)\n\n**Status:** Sketched, needs spec and implementation plan\n\n---\n\nGo get ready. I'll be here when you get back — or in the next session, just say `/hold2` and I'll pull all this up."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52320,"output":256,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774140351476}}
