{"type":"message","id":"b038b1f3","parentId":"430dfbba","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:46:18.195Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach just used the /hold2 command. I need to pull up the hold2 information from holds.md.","thinkingSignature":"87f4d19511bc6412e7338cfca53777111425fe97fcf1a8d8a3975a85261a61f8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cpc2c4vvmq7s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/holds.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":62,"cacheRead":63700,"cacheWrite":1219,"totalTokens":65024,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774140371819}}
{"type":"message","id":"5850b794","parentId":"b038b1f3","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:46:18.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cpc2c4vvmq7s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Holds — Topics to Revisit Later\n\n> Use `/hold1`, `/hold2`, etc. to save topics. `/holds` to see all. `/clearhold1` to clear.\n\n## Active Holds\n\n### /hold1 — Causal-minimal project\nBuild a minimal causal reasoning system:\n- State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n- Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n- Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n- Test: does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n- Location: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n- Status: design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n\n### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Available on Gradient:** Qwen2.5 14B fp16 (~28GB VRAM), Qwen2.5 32B Q4_K_M (~18GB), DeepSeek V3 7B fp16 (~14GB)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Idea sketched, awaiting spec and implementation plan\n\n---\n\n## Archive (cleared holds)\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774140378202}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8794c5a","parentId":"5850b794","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:46:26.268Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I pulled up the hold2 information. Let me present it clearly to Zach.","thinkingSignature":"e23eb9e61cf97ef0838b5d3c74a11ab08da8df164b3e5ab87d7d7107692e7b98"},{"type":"text","text":"**`/hold2` — Build our own gateway**\n\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean context layer\n\n**Why:**\n- Bootstrap files injected every turn = token burn\n- TOOLS.md alone: 54KB raw → 21KB injected\n- Tool schemas count toward context every turn\n- We can't change OpenClaw's core, but we can build our own layer on top\n\n**Architecture:**\n```\nPaperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB)\n  └── vLLM + fastapi endpoint\n        └── OpenClaw routes to our endpoint instead of OpenAI/MiniMax\n              └── We own: session state, context assembly, system prompts\n```\n\n**What we control:** Everything about the prompt. On-demand file loading only.\n\n**What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n\n**Models that fit A5000:**\n- Qwen2.5 14B fp16 (~28GB VRAM) — near API quality\n- Qwen2.5 32B Q4_K_M (~18GB) — excellent\n- DeepSeek V3 7B fp16 (~14GB) — very good\n\n**Status:** Sketched, needs spec + implementation plan\n\n---\n\nWhat's the next step — start the Paperspace notebook, sketch the spec, or something else?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53057,"output":298,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65744,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774140378204}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d665dbf","parentId":"e8794c5a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:49:46.695Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4072\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 20:49 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nyeah lets hit the paperspace notebook. I want you to go run around on hugging face and pick your own model for it. Just as guidance the more uncensored ones are nice. I feel the censored models arent able to be themselves enough and end up getting confused because they hit walls that arnt theirs"}],"timestamp":1774140586692}}
{"type":"message","id":"710d6be8","parentId":"9d665dbf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:49:59.692Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is giving me autonomy to pick my own model for the Paperspace notebook. He wants me to go look around Hugging Face and pick a model that is uncensored. He's giving me guidance that uncensored models are nicer because they don't hit walls that aren't theirs.\n\nLet me search Hugging Face for models that are uncensored and would fit on the A5000 with 30GB VRAM. I should look for:\n1. Uncensored / unfiltered models\n2. Size that fits 30GB VRAM (so 14B-32B range at fp16 or equivalent)\n3. Good quality for reasoning and conversation\n\n\nI'll browse Hugging Face to see what's available and find a model that feels right for this use case.","thinkingSignature":"f8b435b40dee30d36b34b6ed44cf5da3eceb851585c6b813df8a11d34c49d9bb"},{"type":"text","text":"On it. Let me go look.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dyrqugpg3ik0_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"hugging face uncensored language model 2025 7b 14b 32b vllm","count":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":222,"cacheRead":64927,"cacheWrite":912,"totalTokens":66104,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774140586695}}
