 but full content is always generated.\n\nFor a more conservative uncensor that keeps some safety guardrails, check the Balanced variant when it's available.\n\n## Downloads\n\n| File | Quant | Size |\n|------|-------|------|\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-BF16.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/resolve/main/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-BF16.gguf) | BF16 | 65 GB |\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q8_0.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/resolve/main/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q8_0.gguf) | Q8_0 | 35 GB |\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q6_K.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/resolve/main/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q6_K.gguf) | Q6_K | 27 GB |\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q5_K_M.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/resolve/main/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q5_K_M.gguf) | Q5_K_M | 24 GB |\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q4_K_M.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/resolve/main/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q4_K_M.gguf) | Q4_K_M | 20 GB |\n| [Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-IQ4_XS.gguf](https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressiv\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6bf4fff7f07d0fc1\">>>"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774140644494}}
{"type":"message","id":"08777df8","parentId":"d144744a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:51:26.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have the full picture:\n\n- Base model: `Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B` - an MoE model with 35B total params\n- It's multimodal (vision + text)\n- The 35B-A3B means 35B total, ~3B active (A3B = probably \"Active 3B\")\n- MoE models in vLLM need careful handling, but vLLM does support MoE models\n\nFor quantization sizes:\n- BF16: 65GB (too big for A5000)\n- Q8_0: 35GB (too big)\n\n\n- Q6_K: 27GB (too big)\n- Q5_K_M: 24GB (too big)\n- Q4_K_M: 20GB (fits!)\n- IQ4_XS: probably ~18GB (fits)\n\nSo Q4_K_M or IQ4_XS are my best options. Though I'm realizing that with vLLM on Gradient, I might not even need GGUF files—I could potentially load the model directly in a different format first.\n\nBut thinking about the practical setup for Gradient notebooks, GGUF withllama.cpp via a library like `llama-cpp-python` is probably the most straightforward path. Actually, wait—vLLM has pretty solid MoE support now, so I could potentially run the BF16 version directly if I had the 65GB model, but that's way too big for the A5000. The Q4_K_M GGUF at 20GB is the sweet spot: it fits comfortably in the 30GB VRAM and should run well with GGUF support.\n\nThough I'm second-guessing myself on whether Qwen3.5-35B-A3B is actually the best MoE choice here—Qwen3.5 has stronger reasoning capabilities than 2.5, and for a 35B-class MoE, this seems like the right tier. But I should also consider whether a 9B dense model might be more practical depending on the use case.\n\nActually, the 35B MoE is the better pick for quality, so I'll go with that. The model is `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` in Q4_K_M quantization (20GB VRAM), and I should save this to the holds file and let Zach know what I'm thinking.","thinkingSignature":"b9a4b9bfaa2597f8572bd333d7f916960bd3f6f188bad3bb749262d7b0eaa325"},{"type":"text","text":"Got what I need. Here's my pick:\n\n---\n\n**`HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`**\n\n**Why this one:**\n- Qwen3.5 base — the current best open-weights quality\n- 35B total params, ~3B active per token (MoE — memory-efficient)\n- **0/465 refusals** — truly uncensored, no walls, no confusion\n- \"Aggressive\" variant — fully unlocked\n- Multilingual — Qwen3.5 is strong in English and more\n\n**Quantization for A5000 30GB:**\n- `Q4_K_M.gguf` — **20GB** — fits with headroom\n- `IQ4_XS.gguf` — ~18GB — most compressed that keeps quality\n\n**Why not the 9B:** The 9B is great but 35B MoE is a meaningful leap in quality while staying in VRAM budget. Qwen3.5 35B MoE actually approaches GPT-4o territory on some benchmarks. The 9B would be a backup if the 35B is too tight.\n\n---\n\nLet me save this to the hold.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mu6bhpvn9f2t_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/holds.md","oldText":"### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Available on Gradient:** Qwen2.5 14B fp16 (~28GB VRAM), Qwen2.5 32B Q4_K_M (~18GB), DeepSeek V3 7B fp16 (~14GB)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Idea sketched, awaiting spec and implementation plan","newText":"### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Model picked:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active per token, 35B total)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Q4_K_M: 20GB VRAM — fits A5000 30GB with headroom\n  - Base: Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B (multilingual, strong reasoning)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Model picked, awaiting Paperspace notebook setup"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60696,"output":1385,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774140644498}}
