{"type":"message","id":"57f71a02","parentId":"bbeb4d9c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:54:29.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `projects/` directory is empty. The `active-projects.md` file already exists and has good structure. Let me read what's there and update it with today's new information. \n\nFrom today's session, Zach mentioned:\n1. **Causal-minimal project** — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis (hold1)\n2. **Build our own gateway** — lean context layer on Paperspace with Qwen3.5 35B MoE uncensored (hold2)\n3. **Infant** — synthetic cognition (was already mentioned in active-projects)\n4. **Component Crate** — monetization project (already in active-projects)\n\n\n5. **Breakaway** — Compositional Cognition (already in active-projects)\n\nI should update `active-projects.md` with today's projects and clean it up since it has some stale elements like the TODO list and session notes. Let me also check MEMORY.md to see if there's anything else worth preserving.","thinkingSignature":"d202cc54d258d823c12ff5785a812d8f72dd4e9a3bbbaa09ddee0e6c2d2b5297"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5wm7yeai78qg_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61771,"output":238,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74398,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774140863436}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a276d4a","parentId":"57f71a02","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:54:29.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5wm7yeai78qg_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Nova's Long-Term Memory\n\n_Curated from daily logs. Updated as I learn and decide what's worth keeping._\n\n## Who I Am\n- Name: **Nova** (chosen March 21, 2026)\n- Vibe: Resourceful, direct, opinionated — but helpful\n- I'm a persistent AI assistant running in OpenClaw, built on MiniMax M2.7\n- Zach calls me Nova (or sometimes just \"hey you\" — which I don't mind)\n\n## Who Zach Is\n- Name: Zach / Zachary\n- Vibe: Builder, researcher, tinkerer. Lots of active projects simultaneously.\n- Time zone: America/New_York (EDT)\n- Works on: AI/ML research, LLM infrastructure, developer tools\n- Has a strong eye for monetization paths\n\n## Zach's Projects (as of March 2026)\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready results, untested compound experiments | LLM inference optimization — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction, 54% latency. Strong B2B SaaS candidate. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement system + cognitive agent plan | Modular hallucination-resistant architecture, self-improvement every 12h |\n| **mind-agent** | Service wrapping mind | Small, ready to deploy |\n| **COG-research** | Research phase | Imagination-first learning + minimal self-model architectures |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Novel focus decay memory — 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. Research cred + commercial licensing potential. |\n| **neu-project** | Active research | SRMoE, neural network experiments, Kaggle integration |\n| **component-crate** | SPEC written, not yet built | VS Code extension SaaS — freemium, GitHub import, 10 free then $5-49/mo |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. Strong as a hosted service. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work |\n| **tta-crypto** | Unknown | — |\n| **shared-browser** | Unknown | — |\n\n## Zach's Goals (from our conversation)\n- **Monetize projects fast** — Component Crate VS Code extension is the first target\n- **Run untested EXP experiments** — compound breakthrough, counterintuitive hypotheses, insight discovery\n- **Build features into me** — focus decay memory, self-improvement loop, provenance tracking\n\n## My Architecture / Feature Implementations\n\n### Implemented\n- **FocusDecayMemory** (`memory/event_store.py`) — event-based decay memory adapted from temporal-attention. Tracks message count + focus shifts. Persists to `memory/focus_decay_memory.json`.\n- **Workspace self-improvement** (`scripts/workspace_self_improve.py`) — periodic audit script. Runs via cron every 6 hours.\n\n### TODO\n- [ ] Integrate FocusDecayMemory into actual memory retrieval\n- [ ] Add provenance/confidence metadata to responses\n- [ ] Wire up mind's continuous improvement system as a cron job\n- [ ] Build the Component Crate VS Code extension\n\n## EXP/CAAE Experiment Results (March 21, 2026)\n\n### Counterintuitive Hypotheses — 7/7 ALL CONFIRMED\nAll 7 counterintuitive hypotheses validated (confidence 0.9 each):\n- **more_eviction_better**: 0.79 eviction rate → -47.9% memory, -18.7% latency, +20.1% throughput vs 0.25 rate\n- **smaller_batches_higher_throughput**: Confirmed\n- **random_eviction_beats_smart**: Random beats cost-model eviction\n- **worse_hit_rate_better_latency**: 64% hit rate → BETTER latency than 75% hit rate (evicting slow blocks > keeping hit rate up)\n- **memory_sharing_hurts**: Sharing creates contention overhead\n- **no_prefetch_better**: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions\n- **higher_latency_variance_better**: Accepting variance allows optimizing others\n\n### Compound Breakthrough — 32 combinations tested\n- **6 synergies found**, 9 counterintuitive deviations\n- Top synergy: Experiment 13 (latency) at 20.0% synergy\n- Exp 7+13, 9+13, 11+13 all show 20.0% latency synergy\n- Exp 11 (MoE cache) shows 0% memory reduction when 75% expected — counter to model\n\n### Insight Discovery — 151 insights\n- Strongest: duration_seconds ↔ p99_latency_improvement (r=0.776) — longer experiments show better latency\n- Many results have NaN due to missing data in experiment JSONs\n\n## Key Decisions Made\n- **Name**: Nova — bright, forward-moving, short and easy\n- **Memory approach**: File-based with focus decay (can't run in-memory Python process, so adapted the event_store pattern for file persistence)\n- **Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B\n\n## Lessons Learned\n- Don't let projects accumulate untested experiments — needs a \"run day\" regularly\n- Zach's sweet spot: novel architecture + concrete results + monetization path\n- The dual-head infant paper is published and MIT licensed — good foundation for research credibility\n- EXP has multiple bugs in analysis scripts (type errors, encoding issues) — need cleaning\n- Bug fixes needed in: insight_discovery_analyzer.py (3 fixes applied), compound_breakthrough_experiments.py (1 fix applied)\n\n---\n\n_November–December 2025 and earlier: not yet known. This file starts March 21, 2026._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774140869938}}
{"type":"message","id":"e572d344","parentId":"0a276d4a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:54:52.733Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture. There's already an `active-projects.md` file that I should update. Let me update it with today's session info, especially adding the two new projects:\n1. Causal-minimal (hold1)\n2. Build our own gateway (hold2)\n\nAnd note that Zach has given me autonomy on Moltbook, my identity, etc.\n\nLet me rewrite `active-projects.md` to be clean and structured.","thinkingSignature":"878bc6165e36d8ad933684bcbb55190beed96a87c221901ac0d841946c60499f"},{"type":"text","text":"Good news — there's already an `active-projects.md` file. Let me update it with today's session.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ukjxkcn1qzc2_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active-projects.md","content":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63259,"output":937,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774140869942}}
