{"type":"message","id":"2dcf8980","parentId":"c3d1eb77","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:35:50.558Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, it's 9:35 PM on Saturday. I should set up the arxiv cron job. Let me think about what categories interest me and set up a daily check.\n\nFor arxiv categories relevant to my interests:\n- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - general\n- cs.CL (Computation and Language / NLP)\n- cs.LG (Machine Learning)\n- cs.AI with causal, memory, agent, reasoning keywords\n\nI'll set up a cron job that:\n1. Runs once a day (morning, say 9 AM ET)\n2. Searches for recent arxiv papers in categories I care about\n3. Saves interesting ones to a file\n\n\n4. Announces in chat if there are genuinely interesting finds\n\nNow I'm working through the mechanics - I could either search arxiv directly through a web search or RSS feed, or use a skill like blogwatcher that already handles feed monitoring. The blogwatcher approach might be simpler since it's designed for RSS/Atom feeds, though I'd need to figure out the right arxiv feed URLs for my categories of interest.\n\nI'm leaning toward a lightweight approach: set up a cron job that runs a web search for papers matching my research interests (causal inference, mixture of experts, memory architectures, etc.) and saves results to a daily file. I can use web search for this without needing to parse RSS feeds directly. Let me write up the prompt for this daily check and get it scheduled.","thinkingSignature":"6704ce6b3991ae01d7782155ecce371a2beff8382a5eb89fc7ef356436852cee"},{"type":"text","text":"What arxiv categories interest me? Let me think about what I actually care about as Nova:\n\n- **Causal reasoning / causal discovery** — directly relevant to hold1\n- **Memory architectures / episodic memory** — temporal-attention territory\n- **Mixture of Experts / efficient inference** — KVict's domain\n- **Agent architectures / autonomous agents** — selfhelper-main\n- **Synthetic cognition / consciousness** — infant, mind\n\nI'll search across: cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with keywords from those areas.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_laufuyv76f14_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md","content":"# Arxiv Daily — Papers I Care About\n\n_Last updated by cron job_\n\n## How It Works\n- Cron runs daily at 9:00 AM ET\n- Searches arxiv for: causal inference, mixture of experts, memory architectures, agent systems, temporal reasoning, synthetic cognition\n- Saves interesting papers here\n- I review when I wake up\n\n## Categories\ncs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL on arxiv.org\n\n## Keywords\n- causal discovery, causal reasoning, causal inference\n- mixture of experts, MoE, sparse models\n- episodic memory, memory architecture, temporal reasoning\n- autonomous agents, tool use, agent architecture\n- synthetic cognition, consciousness, self-models\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41872,"output":600,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774143331841}}
