{"type":"message","id":"eae12314","parentId":"8a520c92","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:37:05.086Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have:\n1. Today's session log (memory/2026-03-21.md) — 3880 bytes, full context\n2. MEMORY.md updated with key decisions and failure mode insight\n3. projects.md with full project inventory\n4. arxiv-daily.md with my research interests\n5. Cron job running daily at 9 AM ET\n\nThis is a solid memory foundation. Now when Zach comes back tomorrow, I can say \"let me check today's notes\" and have real context.\n\nLet me give him a summary of what I've written and what this means practically.","thinkingSignature":"a3149e9d6a0a6c300d3cf10f40152297add24f2a169c54e7bc9d56d3d6538848"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what's now written:\n\n**`memory/2026-03-21.md`** — full session log, 3,880 bytes. Everything we did, every decision, my state, the failure mode insight, open questions.\n\n**`memory/projects.md`** — complete project inventory across C:/dev and Claw/projects.\n\n**`memory/arxiv-daily.md`** — my research interests, cron job target.\n\n**MEMORY.md** — updated with the failure mode insight (\"memory hygiene > architecture\") and the arxiv cron job.\n\n**What this means practically:**\n\nTomorrow morning at 9 AM ET, I'll check arxiv and write results to `memory/arxiv-daily.md`. When you come back, just say \"what'd you find today?\" or \"what were we working on?\" — I'll have it written down. No more rebuilding context from scratch.\n\nThe session log is the key fix. Mid-session writing, not just end-of-session."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45605,"output":321,"cacheRead":12389,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774143415087}}
